Template: yaboot-installer/bootdev
Type: select
Choices: ${devices}
Default: invaliddevice
Description: On which device should yaboot be installed?
 Yaboot (the Linux bootloader) needs to be installed on a hard disk in
 order for your system to be bootable.  You must pick from the
 available hard disks which have "Apple_Bootstrap" partitions available.

Template: yaboot-installer/no-valid-bootdev
Type: note
Description: No bootstrap partition found
 No hard disks were found which have an "Apple_Bootstrap" partition.
 You must create an 800k HFS partition, with type "Apple_Bootstrap".
